111169.name: Abduction Ray
111169.text: Get a random Demon. Reduce its Cost by (2). Repeatable this turn.

110947.name: Ace Wayfinder
110947.text: Battlecry: Gain two random Bonus Effects. The next Draenei you play gains them as well.

110880.name: Airlock Breach
110880.text: Summon a 5/5 Undead with Taunt and give your hero +5 Health. Spend 5 Corpses to do it again.
110880.flavorText: Open the pod bay doors, Maladaar.

112045.name: Alien Encounters
112045.text: Summon two 2/4 Beasts with Taunt. Costs (1) less for each card you Discovered this game.
112045.flavorText: Close encounters of the cuddly kind.

110840.name: Anchorite
110840.text: Whenever another minion is Overhealed, give it that much extra Health.
110840.flavorText: A Priest is nothing without their anchor. Wait, what?

111301.name: Archimonde
111301.text: Battlecry: Summon every Demon you played this game that didn't start in your deck.
111301.flavorText: Archimonde joined Sargeras in search of power, and in doing so became one of the strongest forces within the Burning Legion who laid waste to countless planets… but in the end he still lost to a wisp.

110091.name: Arkonite Defense Crystal
110091.flavorText: I was just asking if that's what you wanted your Starship to look like, there's no need to get defensive.

110893.name: Arkonite Revelation
110893.text: Draw a card. If it's a spell, it costs (1) less.
110893.flavorText: And if it's a rkonite, revel in it.

111345.name: Arkwing Pilot
111345.text: At the end of your turn, deal 3 damage to a random enemy. Spellburst: Summon an Arkwing Pilot.
111345.flavorText: Delivered in under 30 minutes, or your Arkwings are free!

113171.name: Artanis
113171.text: Battlecry: Summon two 3/4 Zealots with Charge. Your Protoss minions cost (2) less this game.
113171.flavorText: Artanis will forge a new future for the protoss, even if it means destroying everything they ever knew.

111020.name: Askara
111020.text: Battlecry: The next Draenei you play summons a copy of itself.

110891.name: Astral Phaser
110891.text: Choose One - Deal 2 damage to two random enemy minions; or Make one Dormant for 2 turns.
110891.flavorText: Ok, Mom, in this ONE instance it IS a phase.

111305.name: Astral Vigilant
111305.text: Battlecry: Get a copy of the last Draenei you played.
111305.flavorText: Draenei are so dedicated that they remain vigilant even in death.

111412.name: Astrobiologist
111412.text: Battlecry: At the start of your next turn, Discover a spell.
111412.flavorText: Biologists spend a semester abroad. Astrobiologists spend a semester aboard.

111680.name: Auchenai Death-Speaker
111680.text: After another friendly minion is Reborn, summon a copy of it.
111680.flavorText: He sees no evil. He hears no evil. Eh, he speaks a little evil.

111176.name: Bad Omen
111176.text: In 2 turns, summon two 6/6 Demons with Taunt. If you're building a Starship, summon them now.
111176.flavorText: What good is a sign from alien life if I CAN'T EVEN READ IT?!

112812.name: Baneling Barrage
112812.text: Get a 1/1 Baneling that explodes. If you control a Zerg minion, get another Baneling.

111596.name: Barrel Roll
111596.text: Deal 5 damage to an undamaged character. Costs (1) if you're building a Starship.
111596.flavorText: "We're not even close to Draenor, just do the trick! It'll be fiiiine!"

110239.name: Biopod
110239.text: Deathrattle: Deal damage equal to this minion's Attack to a random enemy. Starship Piece

111178.name: Black Hole
111178.flavorText: That's right! The square goes in the black hole.

111899.name: Blasteroid
111899.text: Battlecry: Shuffle 5 random Fire spells into your deck. They cost (2) less.

111897.name: Blazing Accretion
111897.text: Battlecry: Destroy the top 3 cards of your deck. Any Fire spells or Elementals are drawn instead.
111897.flavorText: Much like the Draenei, this Elemental just wants a place to call home. Unlike the Draenei, it incinerates everything it touches.

113192.name: Blink
113192.text: Draw a Protoss minion. Combo: It costs (2) less.
113192.flavorText: Highly mobile. Solid range. Awful at staring contests.

110743.name: Bolide Behemoth
110743.text: Battlecry: Your Asteroids deal 1 more damage this game. Spellburst: Shuffle 3 of them into your deck.
110743.flavorText: There's only so many words that exist for rocks in space.

111415.name: Braingill
111415.text: Battlecry: Give all friendly Murlocs "Deathrattle: Draw a card."

110902.name: Captain's Log
110902.text: Draw 2 cards. Costs (1) less for each Draenei you control.
110902.flavorText: Akama loves a nice comfy log to captain on.

113174.name: Carrier
113174.text: At the end of your turn, summon four 4/1 Interceptors that attack random enemies.
113174.flavorText: Yeah, my teammates always call me this.

111651.name: Celestial Aura
111651.text: While you have exactly 1 minion in play, its Attack and Health are 10. Lasts turns.

113163.name: Chrono Boost
113163.text: Draw 2 Protoss cards. Summon a 3/4 Zealot with Charge.
113163.flavorText: Just think of all the tempests I can make! ...Ah, who am I kidding? I'm just going to use this on probes.

113177.name: Colossus
113177.text: Battlecry: Deal damage to all enemies, twice. (Improved by Protoss spells you cast this game!)

113212.name: Concussive Shells
113212.text: Deal 2 damage and gain 2 Armor. Your next Starship launch costs (2) less.
113212.flavorText: Zerg patients rated these a solid 7 on the pain chart.

113173.name: Construct Pylons
113173.text: Your next Protoss card this turn costs (2) less.

113667.name: Consume
113667.text: Remove 1 Durability from a friendly location to restore 8 Health to your hero.
113667.flavorText: What are you looking at? This isn't a mukbang.

114581.name: Cosmic Phenomenon
114581.text: Summon three 2/3 Elementals with Taunt. If your board is full, give your minions +1/+1.
114581.flavorText: Which one you ask? Uhh, all of them.

110852.name: Cosmonaut
110852.text: Battlecry: Discover a spell from your deck. Reduce its Cost by (5).
110852.flavorText: It might look like they're underwater, but they're cosmo-not!

112869.name: Creep Tumor
112869.text: Your Zerg minions have +1 Attack and Rush. Lasts 3 turns.
112869.flavorText: "If you spot one of these, back away or burn it to hell. Never fight on their turf."

110564.name: Crimson Commander
110564.text: Battlecry and Deathrattle: Give all Draenei in your hand +1/+1.
110564.flavorText: "Wait… why do I have a Deathrattle?"

111304.name: Crystal Welder
111304.flavorText: For all you weld-heads out there, this flavor text is a deep cut.

110911.name: Crystalline Greatmace
110911.text: After your hero attacks, give all Draenei in your hand +2 Attack.
110911.flavorText: The only difference between a mace and a greatmace is... PRESENTATION!

113165.name: Dark Templar
113165.text: Stealth. Battlecry: Destroy an enemy minion. Play another Templar to merge into an Archon!

111973.name: Deep Space Curator
111973.text: Spellburst: Get a random minion of the spell's Cost. Set its Cost to (0).
111973.flavorText: *Gestures to empty room* "...and here is my curated collection of space."

111071.name: Detailed Notes
111071.text: Discover a Beast that costs (5) or more. Reduce its Cost by (2).
111071.flavorText: The Rangari Scouts pride themselves on their highly accurate notes.

110108.name: Dimensional Core
110108.flavorText: At the core of every Starship is a Naaru giving its own energy as a power source. At the core of every Draenei is their unbridled faith in the Naaru.

110908.name: Dirdra, Rebel Captain
110908.text: Rush. Battlecry: Shuffle all 8 Crewmates into your deck. Deathrattle: Draw two Crewmates.
110908.flavorText: Under Velen's command, the Draenei avoid engaging with the enemy in fear of eradication. Under Dirdra's command, the Voronei fight the Legion head on in hopes of eradication.

114584.name: Distress Signal
114584.text: Summon two random 2-Cost minions. Refresh 2 Mana Crystals.
114584.flavorText: HELP! HEEELP! MY OPPONENT PLAYED CARDS!

111300.name: Divine Star
111300.text: Deal 3 damage to a minion. Give a random minion in your hand +3 Health.
111300.flavorText: I could really use a wish right now.

111303.name: Doommaiden
111303.text: Battlecry: Draw a card from your opponent's deck. If you don't play it this turn, put it back.
111303.flavorText: You merely adopted the doom. I was maiden it.

110917.name: Dwarf Planet
110917.text: Fill your board with random 2-Cost minions that attack random enemies.
110917.flavorText: Hey, who let Magni Bronzebeard, who we all know is famous for his Magni Touch, land on this planet!?

110886.name: Eldritch Being
110886.flavorText: Tor flud huth respa di blarry? Fleebletor glomdor!

111075.name: Emergency Meeting
111075.text: Get two 4/4 Crewmates. Put a random Demon that costs (3) or less between them.
111075.flavorText: You installed a big flashing red button on the ship and expected me NOT to press it?

111981.name: Eredar Brute
111981.text: Taunt, Lifesteal Costs (1) less for each enemy minion.
111981.flavorText: After a while, the glowing purple stress ball became ineffective at containing his rage.

111410.name: Escape Pod
111410.flavorText: You can only have two in your deck because we are confident that the Draenei will never run into any dire situations that would warrant any more!

111972.name: Ethereal Oracle
111972.flavorText: I see 2 spells in my future.

113671.name: Evolution Chamber
113671.text: Give your minions +1 Attack. Give your Zerg an extra +1/+1.
113671.flavorText: "Survival of Swarm dependent on evolution, iteration. Trust process, trust sequences. Swarm will not fail." - Abathur

110922.name: Exarch Akama
110922.text: After this attacks, all other friendly minions can attack again (except Exarch Akama).
110922.flavorText: Akama fiercely led the Vindicators in the Draenei's quest to find a new home. If only he knew what would await him on the planet of Draenor…

111893.name: Exarch Hataaru
111893.text: Battlecry: Discover a spell and reduce its Cost by (1). If you play it this turn, repeat this effect.
111893.flavorText: Severely outmatched by the Burning Legion, the Draenei had no hopes of survival… That changed with the invention of arkonite crystals, giving Hataaru and his Artificers new ways to empower their people.

111682.name: Exarch Maladaar
111682.text: Battlecry: The next card you play this turn costs Corpses instead of Mana.
111682.flavorText: The Auchenai order was founded to preserve the memory of Draenei that have passed. But why stop at remembrance when they can live once more?

111074.name: Exarch Naielle
111074.text: Battlecry: Replace your Hero Power with Tracking (Discover a card from your deck).
111074.flavorText: The Great Dark Beyond is vast, with each world containing unknown wonders and horrors alike. To distinguish between the two, Naielle leads the Rangari in surveying all planets the Draenei set foot on.

111009.name: Exarch Othaar
111009.text: Battlecry: If you're building a Starship, get 3 different Arcane spells and reduce their Costs by (2).
111009.flavorText: The temptation of limitless knowledge led some Eredar to join the Burning Legion. In the Sha’tari Draenei, the study of everything lives on.

110904.name: Expedition Sergeant
110904.text: Battlecry: The next Draenei you play immediately attacks a random enemy.

110867.name: Extraterrestrial Egg
110867.text: Deathrattle: Summon a 3/5 Beast that attacks the lowest Health enemy.
110867.flavorText: I'll have mine starry-side up please.

110876.name: Farseer Nobundo
110876.text: Deathrattle: Open the Galaxy's Lens. It absorbs the power of the next spell you cast.
110876.flavorText: "Someone help me! I'm stuck in a net!"

110113.name: Felfire Thrusters
110113.text: Spellburst: Deal this minion's Attack damage to 2 random enemy minions. Starship Piece
110113.flavorText: The coolness factor of a fire decal is universal.

110237.name: Felfused Battery
110237.text: After this attacks, give your other minions +1 Attack. Starship Piece
110237.flavorText: Dirdra is a big believer in green energy.

111008.name: Final Frontier
111008.text: Discover a 10-Cost minion from the past. Set its Cost to (1).

111133.name: Foreboding Flame
111133.text: Battlecry: Demons that didn't start in your deck cost (1) less this game.
111133.flavorText: "I am the harbinger of the end times! Soon, destruction will reign and chaos will ensue in the culmination of your demise: waking up 15 minutes before your alarm!"

111182.name: Galactic Crusader
111182.text: Taunt Deathrattle: Get two random Holy spells. They cost (3) less.
111182.flavorText: The will was very specific that in the event of the Crusader's death, you were to inherit these random spells. Very odd.

112912.name: Ghost
112912.text: Stealth. Battlecry: If you're building a Starship, destroy the lowest-Cost card in your opponent's hand.

110870.name: Gorm the Worldeater
110870.text: Dormant for 5 turns. At the end of your turn, destroy the minion to the right of this to awaken 1 turn sooner.
110870.flavorText: His diet consists of entire WORLDS! Because moons upset his tummy.

111424.artistName: L. Lullabi & I. Campelo da Silva
111424.name: Gravity Lapse
111424.text: Set EVERY minion's Attack and Health to the lower of the two.
111424.flavorText: Did someone forget to pay the gravity bill?

113249.name: Grunty
113249.text: Battlecry: Summon four random Murlocs, then shoot them at enemy minions. (You pick the targets!)

110117.name: Guiding Figure
110117.text: Spellburst: Trigger a random friendly minion's Deathrattle. Starship Piece

113176.name: Hallucination
113176.text: Summon a copy of a friendly Protoss minion. It takes double damage.
113176.flavorText: "Protoss? In our base? I think you're seeing things."

111934.name: Headhunt
111934.text: Deal 2 damage. Get a 4/4 Crewmate with a random Bonus Effect.
111934.flavorText: Even though the red lenses blurred his vision and greatly inhibited his ability to make out color and detail, he looked cool as heck.

111177.name: Healthstone
111177.text: Tradeable Restore all damage your hero has taken this turn. ( )

110235.name: Heart of the Legion
110235.flavorText: It grew 3 sizes after trying to steal Winter Veil.

113855.name: Hellion
113855.text: Your other minions have +1 Attack. (Transforms if you launched a Starship this game.)
113855.flavorText: Let's upgrade to the non-flammable tires next time.

113739.name: High Templar
113739.text: Battlecry: Deal 2 damage to all enemies. Play another Templar to merge into an Archon!
113739.flavorText: If this job doesn't work out, I can always fall back on being a Psionic Storm Chaser.

112834.name: Hive Queen
112834.text: At the end of your turn, get a Larva that transforms into random Zerg minions.
112834.flavorText: Her favorite game is "The Floor is Larva."

110566.name: Hologram Operator
110566.flavorText: Help me, Temporary Draenei. You're my only hope!

110896.name: Hostile Invader
110896.text: Battlecry, Spellburst, and Deathrattle: Deal 2 damage to all other minions.
110896.flavorText: "And my Axe!" "And my Axe!" "And my Axe!"

112859.name: Hydralisk
112859.text: Battlecry: Deal 2 damage to a random enemy. Repeat for each other Zerg minion you control.

113735.name: Immortal
113735.text: Taunt, Divine Shield Battlecry: Spend 4 Mana to double this minion's stats.

111139.name: Infernal Stratagem
111139.text: Give a minion +3/+3. If it's a Demon, your next one costs (2) less.
111139.flavorText: Archimonde INSISTS on calling it a stratagem instead of a strategy because it "sounds cooler."

112830.name: Infestor
112830.text: Deathrattle: Your Zerg minions have +1 Attack for the rest of the game.
112830.flavorText: Even if you survive its neural parasite, you will never live it down.

114513.name: Infiltrate
114513.text: Choose a minion. Deal 3 damage to all other minions.
114513.flavorText: Everybody get out of here! Except you. You can stay.

111346.name: Ingenious Artificer
111346.text: Battlecry: The next Draenei you play refreshes Mana Crystals equal to its Attack.
111346.flavorText: He always brags that he's at the top of the bell curve.

110573.name: Interstellar Starslicer
110573.text: Battlecry and Deathrattle: Reduce the Cost of your Librams by (1) this game.
110573.flavorText: The universe is infinite. Ever-expanding, its sheer size is something that even the ancestors of our ancestors can only dream of knowing. And even still, across every single pocket of the galaxy, every one thing is unique. So, no, we've never made the same flavor-text twice, IDK what you're talking about.

110562.name: Interstellar Wayfarer
110562.text: Divine Shield Battlecry: Reduce the Cost of your Librams by (1) this game.
110562.flavorText: This card is way fairer than most.

110899.name: Jettison
110899.text: Discover a spell. Spend 2 Armor to Discover another.

112815.name: Jim Raynor
112815.text: Battlecry: Relaunch every Starship that you launched this game.
112815.flavorText: He’s lost his faith, his friends, and his beloved, but he still believes that one day, he can make things right again.

111179.name: K'ara, the Dark Star
111179.text: Spellburst: Steal 2 Health from a random enemy. (Shadow spells don't remove this Spellburst.)
111179.flavorText: Velen had never seen a shooting star in real life, so when the opportunity arose…

110842.name: K'ure, the Light Beyond
110842.text: Spellburst: Summon a random 3-Cost minion. (Holy spells don't remove this Spellburst.)
110842.flavorText: The Draenei's story of survival should instill hope in you that anything is possible!! As long as you have the aid of an interdimensional manifestation of holy energy.

112846.name: Kerrigan, Queen of Blades
112846.text: Battlecry: Summon two 2/5 Hive Queens. Deal 3 damage to all enemies.
112846.flavorText: Betrayed by the terrans, she is determined to use the power of the zerg Swarm for her revenge.

112361.name: Kil'jaeden
112361.text: Battlecry: Replace your deck with an endless portal of Demons. Each turn, they gain an additional +2/+2.
112361.flavorText: With complete control of the Burning Legion's forces, Kil'jaeden will stop at nothing until all of the traitorous Draenei have been squelched. *right clicks the enemy hero*

111073.name: Laser Barrage
111073.text: Deal 3 damage to a minion. If you're building a Starship, also damage its neighbors.
111073.flavorText: "I say we take off and laser barrage the entire site from orbit - it's the only way to be sure."

111644.name: Libram of Clarity
111644.text: Draw 2 minions. If this costs (0), give them +2/+1.
111644.flavorText: Ah, I get it! I should play this for 0 Mana.

111647.name: Libram of Divinity
111647.text: Give a minion +3/+3. If this costs (0), return this to your hand at the end of your turn.

111650.name: Libram of Faith
111650.text: Summon three 3/3 Draenei with Divine Shield. If this costs (0), give them Rush.
111650.flavorText: They used to do leaps of faith until Maraad fell into the void.

113211.name: Lift Off
113211.text: Draw 2 Terran cards. Summon a 2/1 Starship Piece with an effect when launched.
113211.flavorText: It's a bird! It's a plane! It's a burning command center slowly moving to the corner of the map!

111991.name: Lightfused Manasaber
111991.flavorText: Oh no, I ran out of fused Mana!

111076.name: Lightspeed
111076.text: Give a minion +1/+2 and Rush. Repeatable this turn.

112876.name: Lock On
112876.text: Set a minion’s Health to 1. Your next Starship launch costs (2) less.
112876.flavorText: Time to lock in. *ahem* I mean lock on.

111292.name: Lucky Comet
111292.text: Discover a Combo minion. The next one you play triggers its Combo twice.
111292.flavorText: When you wish upon a star, your dreams will take you very far. When you wish upon a comet, your luck will make your opponent...

111918.name: Lumia
111918.text: Lifesteal After a hero takes damage, they become Immune for the rest of the turn.
111918.flavorText: "What's a world soul?" "Only the most sophisticated form of life ever protected by Titans. AND it's spherical! SPHERICAL!"

111183.name: Lunar Trailblazer
111183.text: Battlecry: Set the Cost of a random spell in your hand to this minion's Cost.
111183.flavorText: Changing legend into fact, she will ride into history.

112862.name: Lurker
112862.text: After a friendly minion attacks, deal 1 damage to a random enemy (or 2 if your minion is a Zerg).
112862.flavorText: Never typed in chat. Subscribed for 40 months. The perfect viewer.

110872.name: Meteor Storm
110872.text: Deal 5 damage to all minions. Shuffle 5 Asteroids into your deck.
110872.flavorText: "Sir, the possibility of successfully drawing all of your Asteroids in a row are approximately 3,720:1!" "Never tell me the odds!"

113209.name: Missile Pod
113209.text: Starship Piece Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to all enemies. Also triggers on launch.
113209.flavorText: Welcome to the Missile Pod, your one-stop shop for all things missile-related. Tune in each week for developments in the world of missiles.

110744.name: Moonstone Mauler
110744.text: Battlecry: Shuffle 3 Asteroids into your deck that deal damage to a random enemy when drawn.

113203.name: Mothership
113203.text: Taunt Battlecry and Deathrattle: Get two random Protoss minions.
113203.flavorText: You talk to your mothership with that mouth!?

110881.name: Murmur
110881.text: Your Battlecry minions cost (1), but immediately die after being played.

113672.name: Mutalisk
113672.text: Also damages minions next to whomever this attacks (and the enemy hero if a neighbor is missing).
113672.flavorText: A flock of seagulls. A murder of crows. A ball of mutalisks.

111982.name: Mutating Lifeform
111982.text: After this survives damage, gain a random Bonus Effect.
111982.flavorText: Who knows how many amazing discoveries are out there! ... Never mind, I'm going home.

110839.name: Mystified To'cha
110839.text: Battlecry: If the combined Health of both heroes is exactly 42, set your hero's Health to 42.
110839.flavorText: We hired your elementary school math teacher to make this card.

114348.name: Nebula
114348.text: Discover two 8-Cost minions to summon with Taunt and Elusive.

111915.name: Nexus-Prince Shaffar
111915.text: Spellburst: Give a minion in your hand +3/+3 and this Spellburst (unless it already has these effects).
111915.flavorText: Whatever you do, do not give him OR his ethereal parrot a magical lamp.

113576.name: Nydus Worm
113576.text: Draw two Zerg cards. They cost (1) less.
113576.flavorText: How did they fit an ultralisk in there!?

110835.name: Orbital Halo
110835.text: Give a minion +1/+1 and Divine Shield. Costs (0) if you played an adjacent card this turn.
110835.flavorText: I can see your halo. HALO. Haaaalo.

111969.name: Orbital Moon
111969.text: Give a minion Taunt and Lifesteal. If you played an adjacent card this turn, also give it Reborn.
111969.flavorText: The blood moon orbits once again.

111310.name: Orbital Satellite
111310.text: Discover a Draenei. If you played an adjacent card this turn, Discover another.
111310.flavorText: Picks up all the buzz in space.

111010.name: Overzealous Healer
111010.text: Deathrattle: Restore 6 Health to the enemy hero. Spellburst: Silence this minion.
111010.flavorText: In another universe, she's Genji's best friend.

111068.name: Parallax Cannon
111068.text: Has +2 Attack if you've Discovered this turn. Spellburst: Your hero is Immune this turn.
111068.flavorText: Math is now cannon in the Warcraft universe.

112084.name: Perplexing Anomaly
112084.flavorText: I'm so confused... this is really a headscratcher... it doesn't make any sense... why does it cost 3 Mana?

113168.name: Photon Cannon
113168.text: Deal 3 damage. If this kills a minion, your Protoss minions cost (1) less this game.
113168.flavorText: If this card were a minion, it would have Rush.

110865.name: Planetary Navigator
110865.text: Battlecry: The next Draenei you play costs (2) less, but has Overload: (2).

111344.name: Pocket Dimension
111344.text: Discover a spell. Repeat until you see one for the second time.
111344.flavorText: On average, this gets you around 3 cards. And none of them have Overload.

111475.name: Pressure Points
111475.text: Deal 3 damage to a minion. Reduce the Cost of Combo cards in your hand by (1).
111475.flavorText: Have you ever heard of the 5 Point Palm Exploding Heart Technique?

111602.name: Quasar
111602.text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Reduce the Cost of cards in your deck by (3).
111602.flavorText: No one is going to believe that quasars are a real thing, Durg'tash the Sorcerer.

110869.name: Rangari Scout
110869.text: After you Discover a card, get a copy of it.
110869.flavorText: Always takes credit for other people's discoveries.

112062.name: Red Giant
112062.text: Costs (1) less for each adjacent card played while in hand.
112062.flavorText: Lots of cards get played around it, but it's the real star.

111330.artistName: L. Lullabi & I. Campelo da Silva
111330.name: Relentless Wrathguard
111330.text: Battlecry: Deal 2 damage to an enemy minion. If it dies, Discover a Demon.
111330.flavorText: Ugh, for the love of... could they just send a Relenting Smileguard for once!?

113181.name: Resonance Coil
113181.text: Deal 5 damage to a minion. Get a random Protoss spell.
113181.flavorText: This thing can snipe minions three screens away!

112872.name: Roach
112872.text: When you draw this, get a copy of it. Battlecry: If you control another Zerg minion, gain +1/+2.
112872.flavorText: These still aren't as bad as the ones in my old apartment complex.

112820.name: SCV
112820.flavorText: They're called SCVs because they're Super Cool (Very).

112858.name: Salvage the Bunker
112858.text: Summon two 2/2 Marines with Taunt. Your next Starship launch costs (2) less.
112858.flavorText: You just HAD to go with the cheap sheet metal didn't you?

111938.name: Saruun
111938.text: Battlecry: Give all Elementals in your deck Fire Spell Damage +1.
111938.flavorText: BORN FROM THE HEAT DEATH OF COLLIDING SUPERNOVAS, SARUUN SEEKS TO INCINERATE ALL THAT WHICH REVOLVES AROUND THEM TO MERE ASHES AND STARDUST!!!! Which is pretty neato!

111386.name: Scrounging Shipwright
111386.text: Battlecry: Get a random Starship Piece from another class.

113738.name: Sentry
113738.text: Lifesteal. Deathrattle: Your Protoss minions cost (1) less this game.

110111.name: Sha'tari Cloakfield
110111.text: Elusive. Your first spell each turn costs (1) less. Starship Piece
110111.flavorText: The Sha'tari are the reigning champions of interdimensional hide-and-go-seek.

113178.name: Shield Battery
113178.text: Gain 6 Armor. Your next Protoss spell costs (2) less.
113178.flavorText: Hey Artanis, can I use your charger?

110973.name: Shield of Askara
110973.flavorText: One can never have too many shields.

113864.name: Siege Tank
113864.text: Battlecry: Deal 10 damage to a random enemy minion. (Transforms if you launched a Starship this game.)
113864.flavorText: Pretty decent as an off tank, but incredible as a main tank.

111967.name: Solar Flare
111967.text: Deal 2 damage to all enemies. Costs (1) less for each Elemental you control.
111967.flavorText: Saruun is quite the dancer. Their pirouette is deadly.

110878.name: Soulbound Spire
110878.text: Deathrattle: Summon a minion with Cost equal to this minion's Attack (up to 10). Starship Piece
110878.flavorText: Ah yes, EVERY Starship needs a fragile obelisk full of dead people!

112799.name: Spawning Pool
112799.text: Get a 1/1 Zergling. Deathrattle: Your Zerg minions have Rush this turn.
112799.flavorText: Looks more like a spawning hot tub to me, just based on the size.

110119.name: Specimen Claw
110119.text: After your opponent plays a minion, attack it. Starship Piece
110119.flavorText: Great at catching alien species. Not so much their plushies.

113673.name: Spine Crawler
113673.text: Taunt. Can't attack. Has +3 Attack if you control a location.
113673.flavorText: Give him one second, he's rooting! ... Ok give him one more second he's almost done!

112029.name: Splitting Spacerock
112029.flavorText: Space rock. *pew* Spa ce ro ck. *pew* S p a c e r o c k .

111067.name: Spontaneous Combustion
111067.text: Deal 4 damage to a random enemy. If you played an Elemental last turn, choose the target.

110921.name: Spore Empress Moldara
110921.text: Start of Game: Shuffle 7 Replicating Spores into your deck.
110921.flavorText: Sorry for not explaining the Spores in the textbox. We just didn't have that mushroom.

110910.name: Stalwart Avenger
110910.text: Immune while attacking. At the end of EACH turn, swap this minion's Attack and Health.
110910.flavorText: A good defense is a good offense which is a good defense which is a good offense which is a good defense which is a good offense which is a good defense which is a good offense which is a good defense which is a good offense which is a good defense which is a good offense which is a good defense which is a good offense which is a good defense which is a good offense!

111005.name: Star Grazer
111005.text: Elusive, Taunt Spellburst: Give your hero +8 Attack this turn and gain 8 Armor.
111005.flavorText: Star gazing and star grazing aren't too different. Except for the part where you eat stars.

112060.name: Star Vulpera
112060.flavorText: He was a star before he even flew his first ship.

110233.name: Starlight Reactor
110233.text: After you cast an Arcane spell, recast it (targets chosen randomly). Starship Piece

110559.name: Starlight Wanderer
110559.text: Battlecry: The next Draenei you play gains +2/+1.
110559.flavorText: Not all who wander are lost, but some most definitely are and could really use directions right about now.

112856.name: Starport
112856.text: Summon a 2/1 Starship Piece with an effect when launched.
112856.flavorText: Make sure to arrive 3 light-years early for any intergalactic flights.

111180.name: Starscale Constellar
111180.flavorText: You'll understand how to best make use of its effect once you connect the dots.

110110.name: Starship Schematic
110110.text: Discover a Starship Piece from another class. It costs (1) less.
110110.flavorText: It's not plagiarism if you blow up the original ship with lasers.

111181.name: Stranded Spaceman
111181.text: Battlecry: The next Draenei you play gains +2 Health and Rush.
111181.flavorText: Would you say you're floating in a most peculiar way?

111979.name: Suffocate
111979.text: Destroy a minion. If you're building a Starship, also destroy a random neighbor.
111979.flavorText: He's already floating in the void of space. The shadow magic seems like overkill, idk.

111896.name: Supernova
111896.text: Fill your hand with random Fire spells. They cost (1).
111896.flavorText: People who enjoy the heat will say this looks like perfect weather.

111925.name: Talgath
111925.text: Undamaged enemy minions take double damage. Combo: Get a Backstab.
111925.flavorText: Talgath betrayed his people by accepting Sargeras's promise of power. Talgath also saw Velen's refusal of that same power as a betrayal. I'm not convinced Talgath knows what that word means.

112048.name: The 8 Hands From Beyond
112048.text: Battlecry: Destroy both players' decks EXCEPT the 8 highest Cost cards in each.
112048.flavorText: It was a one-eyed, eight-handed, giant purple planet eater.

111914.name: The Ceaseless Expanse
111914.text: Costs (1) less for each time a card was drawn, played, or destroyed. Battlecry: Destroy all other minions.
111914.flavorText: If you play this for its full Mana cost, you know what? You win. Good day sir!

110326.name: The Exodar
110326.text: Battlecry: If you're building a Starship, launch it and choose a Protocol!
110326.flavorText: Limitless potential! Boundless hope! Fourth rate space insurance.

111597.name: The Gravitational Displacer
111597.text: Starship Piece When this is launched, summon a copy of the Starship.
111597.flavorText: You ever wonder why some planets have two moons?

113869.name: Thor
113869.text: Battlecry: Deal 5 damage. (Transforms if you launched a Starship this game.)
113869.flavorText: "I need your clothes, your boots and your chitinous exoskeleton."

110968.name: Triangulate
110968.text: Discover a different spell from your deck. Shuffle 3 copies of it into your deck.
110968.flavorText: "Our mission takes us to the planet of Celes, but I know not of its whereabouts." "Captain, I saw Celes!"

111313.artistName: L. Lullabi & I. Campelo da Silva
111313.name: Troubled Mechanic
111313.flavorText: In space, no one can hear you talk about your troubles.

112866.name: Ultra-Capacitor
112866.text: Starship Piece Battlecry: Gain +1/+1 for each other friendly minion. Also triggers on launch.
112866.flavorText: If my calculations are correct, when this baby hits 88 miles per hour...

113664.name: Ultralisk Cavern
113664.text: Deal 1 damage to all enemies. Deathrattle: Summon an 8/8 Ultralisk with Rush.
113664.flavorText: Don't let your ultralisk get stuck on a ramp.

113677.name: Ultraviolet Breaker
113677.text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage to an enemy minion. Shuffle 3 Asteroids into your deck.
113677.flavorText: You're gonna need more sunscreen. Good thing we stocked up last expansion.

110940.name: Uluu, the Everdrifter
110940.text: Each turn this is in your hand, gain two random Choose One choices. Choose One - ; or .
110940.flavorText: Uluu is such a tryhard, he's carrying an entire planet!

110914.name: Unyielding Vindicator
110914.text: Battlecry: The next Draenei you play gives your hero its Attack for that turn.
110914.flavorText: Strike and smash, until it is done.

112028.name: Ur'zul Rager
112028.flavorText: The Burning Legion is host to many horrors, but a 3 Mana 5/1 is the worst of all!

111306.name: Velen, Leader of the Exiled
111306.text: Taunt. Deathrattle: Trigger the Battlecries and Deathrattles of all other Draenei you played this game.
111306.flavorText: For an exiled dude, he's pretty popular!

113663.name: Viper
113663.text: Battlecry: Summon a minion from your opponent's hand. Your other Zerg minions gain Reborn and attack it.

113733.name: Void Ray
113733.flavorText: Raymond just had this empty feeling.

111906.name: Voronei Recruiter
111906.text: At the end of your turn, get a 4/4 Crewmate with a random Bonus Effect.
111906.flavorText: He has an eyepatch but isn't a Pirate. He's a Recruiter but doesn't Recruit. Smh my head.

111678.name: Wakener of Souls
111678.flavorText: The alarm again!? Wake me up in 5 more eternities.

111937.name: Warp Drive
111937.text: Draw 2 cards. If you're building a Starship, they cost (2) less.

113164.name: Warp Gate
113164.text: Your next Protoss minion costs (3) less.
113164.flavorText: This is gonna be really meta-warping.

110923.name: Xor'toth, Breaker of Stars
110923.text: Battlecry: Add two Stars to both sides of your hand. When they collide, deal 5 damage to all enemies.
110923.flavorText: We started his stats at 50,000,000,000/50,000,000,000 to be lore-accurate, but it was just a nudge too powerful.

112873.name: Yamato Cannon
112873.text: Starship Piece Battlecry: Destroy a random enemy minion. Also triggers on launch.

111653.name: Yrel, Beacon of Hope
111653.text: Rush Deathrattle: Get three different Librams from an older timeline!
111653.flavorText: Yrel has a lot of overdue library books.

112867.name: Zergling
112867.flavorText: It's all fun and games until 8 of these show up at your door at the 2 minute mark.
